**[Summary]**  
The ticket describes the new warning XAF0033 introduced in version 25.1 of the software, which relates to Entity Framework (EF) business class properties. This warning indicates that business object properties should not be declared with the `new`, `override`, or `abstract` modifiers. The explanation includes examples of invalid and valid code to help developers avoid these issues. The ticket also provides links to relevant documentation for further reference.

**[Subject]** Describe new XAF0033 warning  
**[Description]** For 25.1 we added a new warning, XAF0033. basically it is a mirror of [https://docs.devexpress.com/eXpressAppFramework/403392/debugging-testing-and-error-handling/code-diagnostics/xaf0002](https://docs.devexpress.com/eXpressAppFramework/403392/debugging-testing-and-error-handling/code-diagnostics/xaf0002), but with 2 twists - it is about EF instead of Xpo, and it bans new, abstract and override properties (virtual are allowed):

# XAF0033: EF business class properties should not be overridden

**Severity: Warning**  
XAF and EF do not support the following business object’s properties:

*   Declared with the [`new`][0] keyword.  
*   Overridden properties.  
*   Abstract properties.  

For more information about these requirements, see the following article: [Can I override properties of business objects?][1]. This diagnostic works only for EF classes derived from the [DevExpress.Persistent.BaseImpl.EF.BaseObect][2] class. This diagnostic does not check static properties.

## Examples  
### Invalid Code  

*   C#

```
using DevExpress.Persistent.Base;
using DevExpress.Persistent.BaseImpl.EF;

namespace MySolution.Module.BusinessObjects {
    public class TestClass : BaseObject {
        private int testProperty1; 
        // The property must not override a property from a base class
        //public override int TestProperty1 { // Warning: XAF0033
        //    get { return testProperty1 + 1; }
        //    set { SetPropertyValue(nameof(TestProperty1), ref testProperty1, value); }
        //}

        private int testProperty2; 
        // The property must not be declared with the `new` keyword
        //public new int TestProperty2 { // Warning: XAF0002
        //    get { return testProperty2 + 1; }
        //    set { SetPropertyValue(nameof(TestProperty2), ref testProperty2, value); }
        //}
    }
}
```

### Valid Code  

*   C#

```
using DevExpress.Persistent.Base;
using DevExpress.Persistent.BaseImpl.EF;

namespace MySolution.Module.BusinessObjects {
    public class TestClass : BaseObject {

        private int testProperty;
        // The property that meets the requirements
        public int TestProperty { 
            get { return testProperty; }
            set { SetPropertyValue(nameof(TestProperty), ref testProperty, value); }
        }
    }
}
```

## How to Fix  
Check the business object’s property declaration and ensure the property is declared without the following modifiers:

*   `abstract`  
*   `override`  
*   `new`  

